## 🐛 Bug Report
Alignment -> indent does not work properly. Rest of the alignment options have no issue.

I have saved the workbook with an indent of 3 on that cell. But, the property is not getting saved properly.

![image](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/assets/2245672/c38393c2-d4fc-4ec3-b99e-48e73459a0f7)

Lib version: 4.4.0

This issue is happening with Libreoffice Calc. If I open the file in Microsoft Excel, it does not happen. 

## Steps To Reproduce

```
const ExcelJS = require('exceljs');

const wb = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({filename: 'test.xlsx', useStyles: true});
const ws = wb.addWorksheet('Sheet1');
ws.addRow(["Hello World!"]);
ws.eachRow(row=>{
    row.eachCell(cell=>{
        cell.alignment = {indent: 3};
        cell.font = {bold: true};
    })
})

wb.commit()
```

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

Interestingly, if i try to modify the indent using the UI of libreoffice calc - the indent suddenly becomes 3. 

Checkout the following screenshot. I decreased the indent by 1 using the UI. It seems like the indent property is getting saved somewhere but in a buggy way. I am not sure if this is a Libreoffice Calc issue or an exceljs issue.

![image](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/assets/2245672/02cf0972-8e6c-403e-b19e-bfdf27b203ba)

